ional_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania_men's_national_basketball_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her enormous success\", \"from\": 2657, \"to\": 2677}, {\"ngram\": \"many fans\", \"from\": 2679, \"to\": 2688}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 2692, \"to\": 2701}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold medal\", \"from\": 2760, \"to\": 2774}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2023 world title\", \"from\": 2798, \"to\": 2818}]}, {\"sentence\": \"America's biggest hope for an Olympic gold medal in breaking is with Florida-native Victor \\\"B-boy Victor\\\" Montalvo, according to some experts interviewed for this piece.\", \"from\": 2832, \"to\": 3001, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"America's biggest hope\", \"from\": 2832, \"to\": 2854}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic gold medal\", \"from\": 2859, \"to\": 2880}, {\"ngram\": \"breaking\", \"from\": 2884, \"to\": 2892}, {\"ngram\": \"Florida-native Victor \\\"B-boy Victor\\\" Montalvo\", \"from\": 2901, \"to\": 2946}, {\"ngram\": \"some experts\", \"from\": 2961, \"to\": 2973}, {\"ngram\": \"this piece\", \"from\": 2990, \"to\": 3000}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Breaking consists of four kinds of movement.\", \"from\": 3003, \"to\": 3047, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Breaking\", \"from\": 3003, \"to\": 3011}, {\"ngram\": \"four kinds\", \"from\": 3024, \"to\": 3034}, {\"ngram\": \"movement\", \"from\": 3038, \"to\": 3046}]}, {\"sentence\": \"First is toprock, which is footwork performed by the breaker in a standing position.\", \"from\": 3048, \"to\": 3132, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"toprock\", \"from\": 3057, \"to\": 3064}, {\"ngram\": \"footwork\", \"from\": 3075, \"to\": 3083}, {\"ngram\": \"the breaker\", \"from\": 3097, \"to\": 3108}, {\"ngram\": \"a standing position\", \"from\": 3112, \"to\": 3131}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is also downrock, which is when breakers dance low to the ground and are equally supported by their arms and legs.\", \"from\": 3133, \"to\": 3253, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"downrock\", \"from\": 3147, \"to\": 3155}, {\"ngram\": \"breakers\", \"from\": 3171, \"to\": 3179}, {\"ngram\": \"the ground\", \"from\": 3193, \"to\": 3203}, {\"ngram\": \"their arms\", \"from\": 3233, \"to\": 3243}, {\"ngram\": \"legs\", \"from\": 3248, \"to\": 3252}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, there are power moves, which are more complicated acrobatic moves where the breaker is typically only supported by one body part.\", \"from\": 3254, \"to\": 3389, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"power moves\", \"from\": 3270, \"to\": 3281}, {\"ngram\": \"more complicated acrobatic moves\", \"from\": 3293, \"to\": 3325}, {\"ngram\": \"the breaker\", \"from\": 3332, \"to\": 3343}, {\"ngram\": \"one body part\", \"from\": 3375, \"to\": 3388}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally, there are freezes, where breakers stop all movement and maintain their balance in an often difficult position.\", \"from\": 3390, \"to\": 3509, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"breakers\", \"from\": 3424, \"to\": 3432}, {\"ngram\": \"all movement\", \"from\": 3438, \"to\": 3450}, {\"ngram\": \"their balance\", \"from\": 3464, \"to\": 3477}, {\"ngram\": \"an often difficult position\", \"from\": 3481, \"to\": 3508}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Boos and cheers often decide the winners in the underground scene, according to B-girl Mantis.\", \"from\": 3511, \"to\": 3605, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3598, \"end\": 3604, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mantis\", \"score\": 0.9860588119685983, \"rank\": 0.014137984359382771, \"text\": \"Mantis\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mantis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mantis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Boos\", \"from\": 3511, \"to\": 3515}, {\"ngram\": \"cheers\", \"from\": 3520, \"to\": 3526}, {\"ngram\": \"the winners\", \"from\": 3540, \"to\": 3551}, {\"ngram\": \"the underground scene\", \"from\": 3555, \"to\": 3576}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics' process is more formal, however.\", \"from\": 3606, \"to\": 3652, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympics' process\", \"from\": 3606, \"to\": 3627}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Breakers will take turns battling 1 on 1 over a series of three, one-minute rounds, to music that will be played by a DJ.\", \"from\": 3654, \"to\": 3775, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Breakers\", \"from\": 3654, \"to\": 3662}, {\"ngram\": \"turns\", \"from\": 3673, \"to\": 3678}, {\"ngram\": \"a series\", \"from\": 3700, \"to\": 3708}, {\"ngram\": \"three, one-minute rounds\", \"from\": 3712, \"to\": 3736}, {\"ngram\": \"music\", \"from\": 3741, \"to\": 3746}, {\"ngram\": \"a DJ\", \"from\": 3770, \"to\": 3774}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to the International Olympic Committee, nine judges will score athletes' performances based on these five factors: technique, vocabulary, musicality, execution and originality, with the last two categories counting the most.\", \"from\": 3777, \"to\": 4011, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3794, \"end\": 3825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nine judges\", \"from\": 3827, \"to\": 3838}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes' performances\", \"from\": 3850, \"to\": 3872}, {\"ngram\": \"these five factors\", \"from\": 3882, \"to\": 3900}, {\"ngram\": \"technique\", \"from\": 3902, \"to\": 3911}, {\"ngram\": \"musicality\", \"from\": 3925, \"to\": 3935}, {\"ngram\": \"execution\", \"from\": 3937, \"to\": 3946}, {\"ngram\": \"originality\", \"from\": 3951, \"to\": 3962}, {\"ngram\": \"the last two categories\", \"from\": 3969, \"to\": 3992}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each round will be judged individually and the competitor who wins the most rounds wins gold.\", \"from\": 4012, \"to\": 4105, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each round\", \"from\": 4012, \"to\": 4022}, {\"ngram\": \"the competitor\", \"from\": 4055, \"to\": 4069}, {\"ngram\": \"the most rounds\", \"from\": 4079, \"to\": 4094}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 4100, \"to\": 4104}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yes and no.\", \"from\": 4107, \"to\": 4118, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Local breakers expressed mixed feelings about the art form's global attention.\", \"from\": 4119, \"to\": 4197, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Local breakers\", \"from\": 4119, \"to\": 4133}, {\"ngram\": \"mixed feelings\", \"from\": 4144, \"to\": 4158}, {\"ngram\": \"the art form's global attention\", \"from\": 4165, \"to\": 4196}]}, {\"sentence\": \"John \\\"Flonetik\\\" Vinuya, who owns360 Flow Breaking studioin Kensington, Brooklyn, with his wife B-girl Mantis, acknowledged that the sport's ascendance into mainstream national and international competitions can be great for the upcoming B-boys and B-girl dancers \\\"because they have a goal to reach.\\\"\", \"from\": 4199, \"to\": 4498, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4258, \"end\": 4278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kensington,_Brooklyn\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kensington, Brooklyn\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kensington,_Brooklyn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kensington,_Brooklyn\"}, {\"begin\": 4258, \"end\": 4278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kensington,_Brooklyn\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kensington, Brooklyn\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kensington,_Brooklyn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kensington,_Brooklyn\"}, {\"begin\": 4301, \"end\": 4307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mantis\", \"score\": 0.9860588119685983, \"rank\": 0.014137984359382771, \"text\": \"Mantis\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mantis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mantis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"John \\\"Flonetik\\\" Vinuya\", \"from\": 4199, \"to\": 4221}, {\"ngram\": \"Flow Breaking studioin\", \"from\": 4235, \"to\": 4257}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport's ascendance\", \"from\": 4327, \"to\": 4349}, {\"ngram\": \"mainstream national and international competitions\", \"from\": 4355, \"to\": 4405}, {\"ngram\": \"the upcoming B-boys and B-girl dancers\", \"from\": 4423, \"to\": 4461}, {\"ngram\": \"a goal\", \"from\": 4481, \"to\": 4487}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But he expressed concern that the practice might lose a little of its freewheeling creativity.\", \"from\": 4500, \"to\": 4594, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"concern\", \"from\": 4517, \"to\": 4524}, {\"ngram\": \"the practice\", \"from\": 4530, \"to\": 4542}, {\"ngram\": \"its freewheeling creativity\", \"from\": 4566, \"to\": 4593}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is always going to be a fight between whether breaking is still culture or if it's a sport, now that you can make money off of it,\\\" Flonetik said.\", \"from\": 4596, \"to\": 4749, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a fight\", \"from\": 4625, \"to\": 4632}, {\"ngram\": \"breaking\", \"from\": 4649, \"to\": 4657}, {\"ngram\": \"culture\", \"from\": 4667, \"to\": 4674}, {\"ngram\": \"a sport\", \"from\": 4686, \"to\": 4693}, {\"ngram\": \"money\", \"from\": 4717, \"to\": 4722}, {\"ngram\": \"Flonetik\", \"from\": 4735, \"to\": 4743}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But there is still a lot of us out here that think about that cultural aspect of hip-hop, and we are not trying to commercialize it.\\\"\", \"from\": 4750, \"to\": 4884, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 4770, \"to\": 4775}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 4779, \"to\": 4781}, {\"ngram\": \"that cultural aspect\", \"from\": 4808, \"to\": 4828}, {\"ngram\": \"hip-hop\", \"from\": 4832, \"to\": 4839}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gabriel \\\"Kwikstep\\\" Dionisio is one of the city's original breakers who started in 1981 at age 11.\", \"from\": 4886, \"to\": 4983, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gabriel \\\"Kwikstep\\\" Dionisio\", \"from\": 4886, \"to\": 4913}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's original breakers\", \"from\": 4924, \"to\": 4952}, {\"ngram\": \"age\", \"from\": 4976, \"to\": 4979}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He founded the hip-hop collaborative Full Circle in 1992 with his now wife Ana \\\"Rokafella\\\" Garcia.\", \"from\": 4984, \"to\": 5082, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the hip-hop collaborative\", \"from\": 4995, \"to\": 5020}, {\"ngram\": \"Full Circle\", \"from\": 5021, \"to\": 5032}, {\"ngram\": \"his now wife Ana \\\"Rokafella\\\" Garcia\", \"from\": 5046, \"to\": 5081}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kwikstep said it's great to see the athletes bring attention to the sport, but said that as breaking goes mainstream, it loses some of its earlier elements.\", \"from\": 5084, \"to\": 5240, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kwikstep\", \"from\": 5084, \"to\": 5092}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 5116, \"to\": 5128}, {\"ngram\": \"attention\", \"from\": 5135, \"to\": 5144}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 5148, \"to\": 5157}, {\"ngram\": \"breaking\", \"from\": 5176, \"to\": 5184}, {\"ngram\": \"its earlier elements\", \"from\": 5219, \"to\": 5239}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said that mainstream commercial competitions like the Red Bull BC One competition and now, the Olympics, avoid the high stakes rivalries of more traditional breakdancing.\", \"from\": 5242, \"to\": 5415, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5299, \"end\": 5314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Bull_BC_One\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Red Bull BC One\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Bull_